          <p class='first-para'>
            There have been two reports on drugs in the past 12 months. There is the "United Kingdom Anti-Drugs Co-ordinator's Annual Report 1999/2000", which is vacuous piffle, unscientific, self-admiring and useless. Perhaps that is too generous&#x2014;I tend to be mealy-mouthed whenever I talk about the drug tsar's report. Then there is another report&#x2014;"Drugs and the Law: Report of the Independent Inquiry into the <a href="/acts/misuse-of-drugs-act-1971">Misuse of Drugs Act 1971</a>"&#x2014;which is scientific, authoritative, independent and practical. It was written over two years by a group of policemen and scientists, and it comes up with solutions. The sad thing is that the first report represents the policy both of the Opposition and the Government, and the second does not.</p><p>
            I have listened to the hon. Member for Ribble Valley (Mr. Evans) with some interest. All drugs are damaging, and one should always make one's own position clear. I am a user of drugs&#x2014; I am devoted to wine and beer, in modest quantities. They add a great deal of pleasure to my life and help me to relax.
          </p>
